ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A mostly informal discussion about early modern print culture and the consequences of that research for our practice as literary scholars, with weekly assignments meant to improve our skills as researchers. Yes, I would recommend the class

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Definitely helped me think about the importance of editorial and print practices, and the consequences of book history for other types of literary criticism.Part of a much longer process of figuring out what kind of scholarship I myself want to do. I don't think I'm going to be a book historian, but the course definitely helped me along in defining what exactly it is that I'm interested in. Also provided different ideas for the ways that book history can contribute to other types of projects
